This project is not feasible in one week. A formally-verified consensus protocol requires: (1) protocol specification in Lean 4 (2-3 days minimum), (2) safety proofs (correctness under all conditions—3-5 days for a simple protocol), (3) liveness proofs (progress guarantees—2-3 days), (4) removing axioms through constructive reconstruction (1-2 weeks). A production-ready protocol additionally needs distributed system semantics (message ordering, timing), Byzantine fault tolerance proofs, and validation against attacks—another 2-3 weeks minimum. Realistic scope: 2-3 months for one engineer to deliver a verified Raft-like consensus without axioms and Mathlib. For one week, deliver only: formal specification + safety proof for a simplified synchronous consensus (no Byzantine faults, no liveness), perhaps 500-1000 lines of Lean. This is technically sound but not production-ready. Recommend either extending timeline to 8-12 weeks, expanding the team to 3-4 engineers, or narrowing the protocol to a toy synchronous model with partial proofs.
